etymologies: early 17th century: from late Latin astralis, from astrum ‘star’

definitions: of, connected with, or resembling the stars
relating to a supposed nonphysical realm of existence to which various psychic and paranormal phenomena are ascribed, and in which the physical human body is said to have a counterpart

examples.text: spiritual beings from the astral plane

shortDefinitions: relating to supposed non-physical realm of existence to which various psychic and paranormal phenomena are ascribed
